{"type":"message","id":"6bc17ab9","parentId":"22796aae","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:43:48.384Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mmzs41d1ks27_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 084213\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Key insight identified: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Need to: Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs, measure invariant/variant classification accuracy, predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe immediate next step from the goals is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files I have available to work with.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pulse logs mentioned - `logs/pulse_*.md` files. I should:\r\n\r\n1. First, look at what pulse logs exist and their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory to understand the data I'm working with.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse log files. The most concrete next step is to create the TIC classifier script that analyzes the pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n2. Extracts invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (session-specific) content\r\n3. Attempts next-pulse content prediction\r\n4. Reports classification accuracy against success criteria (>70% invariance detection, >60% next-pulse prediction)\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 TIC Experiment milestone by implementing the core classifier.\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_metadata(filepath: Path) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured metadata from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key-value pairs from observation/action sections\r\n    data = {\r\n        \"timestamp\": PULSE_PATTERN.search(filepath.name).group(1) if PULSE_PATTERN.search(filepath.name) else \"unknown\",\r\n        \"content\": content,\r\n        \"lines\": content.split(\"\\n\"),\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract code blocks (variant - session specific)\r\n    data[\"code_blocks\"] = re.findall(r\"```[\\s\\S]*?```\", content)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals mentions (invariant - persistent across sessions)\r\n    data[\"goal_refs\"] = re.findall(r\"(Phase \\d|PENDING|Goal|Active)\", content, re.IGNORECASE)\r\n    \r\n    return data\r\n\r\ndef identify_invariants(pulses: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Identify content patterns that persist across multiple pulses.\r\n    Invariants = causal structure candidates.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Track phrase frequencies across all pulses\r\n    phrase_counts = Counter()\r\n    phrase_pulses = {}\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        content = pulse[\"content\"]\r\n        # Extract 3+ word phrases\r\n        words = content.split()\r\n        for i in range(len(words) - 2):\r\n            phrase = \" \".join(words[i:i+3]).lower()\r\n            phrase_counts[phrase] += 1\r\n            if phrase not in phrase_pulses:\r\n                phrase_pulses[phrase] = []\r\n            phrase_pulses[phrase].append(pulse[\"timestamp\"])\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants appear in >50% of pulses\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {p: c for p, c in phrase_counts.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"invariant_phrases\": invariants,\r\n        \"total_pulses\": len(pulses),\r\n        \"unique_invariants\": len(invariants)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef identify_variants(pulses: List[Dict]) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Identify content unique to single pulses (session-specific).\"\"\"\r\n    phrase_counts = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        words = pulse[\"content\"].split()\r\n        for i in range(len(words) - 2):\r\n            phrase = \" \".join(words[i:i+3]).lower()\r\n            phrase_counts[phrase] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Variants appear in only 1 pulse\r\n    variants = [p for p, c in phrase_counts.items() if c == 1]\r\n    return variants[:100]  # Top 100\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_pulse: Dict, invariants: Dict, pulses: List[Dict]) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Attempt to predict next pulse content from invariants.\r\n    Returns prediction accuracy score (0-1).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    # Find next pulse in sequence\r\n    current_idx = None\r\n    for i, p in enumerate(pulses):\r\n        if p[\"timestamp\"] == current_pulse[\"timestamp\"]:\r\n            current_idx = i\r\n            break\r\n    \r\n    if current_idx is None or current_idx >= len(pulses) - 1:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    next_pulse = pulses[current_idx + 1]\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction: invariants from current pulse should appear in next\r\n    current_invariants = set(k.lower() for k in current_pulse[\"content\"].split() if len(k) > 4)\r\n    next_content_lower = next_pulse[\"content\"].lower()\r\n    \r\n    # Count how\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:42:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774356228383}}
